# Challah Braiding

Tags: Jewish, baking, bread, challah

# 4-Strand Challah

1. Create four equal-size strands. Lay the four strands side-by-side, then pinch them together so they are connected at the top.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

2. Take the strand **furthest to the right** and weave it towards the left through the other strands using this pattern: **over, under, over**.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%201.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%201.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

3. Take the strand **furthest to the right** and repeat the weaving pattern again: **over, under, over**. Repeat this pattern, always starting with the strand furthest to the right, until the whole loaf is braided.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%202.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%202.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

4. Pinch the ends of the loose strands together and tuck them under on both ends of the challah loaf to create a nice shape.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%203.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%203.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

# Round Challah

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

1. Knead and roll to flatten the dough into a rough rectangular shape, about a 1/2 inch thick.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%204.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%204.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

2. If adding raisins, sprinkle them evenly across the center of the rectangle. 

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%205.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%205.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

3. Use your hands to rolls the dough from the bottom upward into one large, even strand, making sure to roll tightly to avoid air pockets. The raisins will be concealed inside the dough.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%206.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%206.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

4. Roll the dough using both hands to smooth seams and create one large strand.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%207.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%207.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

5. Taper the strand at the ends by rolling the dough between your palms.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%208.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%208.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

6. Roll one end of the strand inward to create a spiral snail-shell shape.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%209.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%209.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

7. Continue rolling the strand in the same direction until the spiral is complete. Tuck the loose end of the spiral underneath the challah and pinch it tightly into the bottom, securing it.

![Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%2010.png](Challah%20Braiding%205916439a119c43c8bb017abc88d1e6d5/Untitled%2010.png)

[data:image/jpeg;base64,](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
